      • getEmptyType

        public static TypeSpec getEmptyType()
        Returns an 'empty' type, which is actually a double with very lax endpoints. Every example will be used to constrain this.

      • addExample

        public void addExample(String example)
        Adds a new example to this TypeSpec. If the new example won't parse as any other TypeSpec.SupportedType, the internal type is set to TypeSpec.SupportedType.STRING. If it parses as a compatible type, the min and max values are modified accordingly.

      • addMinMaxVectors

      • getDoubleValueVector

        public Vector getDoubleValueVector(FlagConfig flagConfig,
                                   double value)
        Returns a vector appropriate for this value by interpolating endpoints. Only for type TypeSpec.SupportedType.DOUBLE.
